                <head>No. 187<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On July 22, 1952, the International Court of Justice supported the claim of the
                    Government of Iran, by nine votes to five, that the Court was without
                    jurisdiction in the Iranian oil nationalization case. For the Court’s opinion,
                    see International Court of Justice, <hi rend="italic">Anglo-Iranian Oil Co. Case
                        (United Kingdom</hi> v. <hi rend="italic">Iran)</hi>, Judgment, July 22,
                    1952.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
